182	- **Scroll behavior:** On scrollable content, the AppBar has a subtle fade-in effect as content scrolls beneath it. On screens with SliverAppBar, the AppBar collapses to show a smaller representation.
183	- **Leading/back button:** Icon button with 48-point touch target, Lavender Bloom on tap
184	
185	---
186	
187	## 5. Layout Principles
188	
189	- **Base spacing unit:** 8 points — all spacing is derived from multiples of 8
190	- **Screen horizontal padding:** 16 points from each edge
191	- **Section vertical spacing:** 24 points between major sections
192	- **Card internal padding:** 16 points all sides
193	- **Card gap:** 12 points between cards in a grid or list
194	- **List item minimum height:** 56 points (comfortable touch target for interactive list items)
195	- **Minimum touch target:** 48 points (compliant with mobile accessibility standards)
196	- **Bottom sheet handle bar:** 40 points wide, 4 points tall, centered 20 points from top
197	- **Safe area awareness:** Respect status bar at top (add 12 points padding when status bar is visible) and home indicator at bottom (bottom navigation and FAB account for this)
198	- **Grid gutters:** 12 points between columns in 2-column grids
199	- **Card corner radius:** 16 points for standard cards; 12 points for smaller card variants
200	
201	---
202	
203	## 6. Motion & Animation
204	
205	Motion is gentle, purposeful, and never jarring. The app feels like a calm, flowing experience rather than a reactive, mechanical one.
206	
207	- **Page transitions:** 300ms duration, smooth deceleration. Screen content slides and fades simultaneously — the new screen appears to gently settle into place.
208	- **Micro-interactions:** 200ms duration, snappy ease-out. Button presses, chip selections, toggle switches — responses feel quick but soft, like a gentle tap on a responsive surface.
209	- **Hero transitions:** 350ms duration, fast-out-slow-in easing. When navigating from a list to a detail view (e.g., article reader), shared elements like images and titles smoothly expand and continue their motion arc.
210	- **Staggered list reveals:** 50ms delay between each item. When content loads, list items cascade into view in a waterfall — items appear 50ms apart, creating a sense of gentle unfolding rather than a sudden dump of content.
211	- **Bottom sheets:** 250ms duration, smooth deceleration. Sheets slide up from the bottom edge, decelerating naturally as they reach their resting position.
212	- **Pull-to-refresh:** 150ms duration, quick snap. The refresh indicator appears and dismisses quickly but not abruptly.
213	- **Tab indicator movement:** 200ms duration, ease-in-out. The active indicator pill smoothly glides between tab positions.
214	- **Card tap feedback:** 200ms ease-out scale to 98%, then 200ms ease-out return to 100%.
215	- **FAB appearance:** 200ms fade-in with subtle scale from 95% to 100%.
216	
217	---
218	
219	## 7. Anti-Patterns (Banned Design Rules)
220	
221	- No default platform colors — every color comes from the design system palette
222	- No ad-hoc text sizing — all text uses the defined type scale
223	- No inconsistent spacing — all spacing uses the 8-point base unit scale
224	- No arbitrary elevation — every shadow level communicates a specific hierarchy
225	- No Inter or Roboto — Nunito is the only font family
226	- No purple or neon AI aesthetic — colors are warm pastels, not synthetic
227	- No generic gradients — backgrounds are flat or subtly tinted, not gradient-washed
228	- No shadows without purpose — elevation always communicates hierarchy
229	- No desktop patterns — no sidebars, hover tooltips, right-click menus, or desktop-only interaction patterns
230	- No touch targets smaller than 48 points
231	- No critical actions outside the thumb zone (bottom two-thirds of screen height)
232	- No pure black (#000000) anywhere — deep charcoal and off-black only
233	- No pure white (#FFFFFF) for text — use off-white tones that reduce eye strain
[2026-05-19T00:31:23.824Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_sgrqnod5zspo_2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# SPEC.md — My Pregnancy (`/pregnancy-progress`)\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Screen Title\n4\t\n5\t**My Pregnancy** — Week-by-week pregnancy progress viewer\n6\t\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\t## 2. Purpose\n10\t\n11\tThe Pregnancy Progress screen allows expecting mothers to explore their pregnancy journey week by week through a horizontal swiper interface. It provides:\n12\t\n13\t- At-a-glance view of current pregnancy week with fruit-size comparison\n14\t- Body change expectations for each week\n15\t- Baby development milestones\n16\t- Actionable self-care tips tailored to each week\n17\t- Due date tracking with countdown and trimester indicator\n18\t\n19\t**Why it exists:** Replaces uncertainty with knowledge — mothers can swipe to any week to understand what's happening in their body and with their baby, building confidence throughout the journey.\n20\t\n21\t---\n22\t\n23\t## 3. Route\n24\t\n25\t```\n26\t/pregnancy-progress\n27\t```\n28\t\n29\t- **Parent:** Home tab (`/`)\n30\t- **Navigation type:** Push (no bottom nav, no FAB)\n31\t- **Swipe-back:** Returns to Home\n32\t\n33\t---\n34\t\n35\t## 4. Widget Name\n36\t\n37\t```\n38\tPregnancyProgressScreen\n39\t```\n40\t\n41\tFile: `lib/screens/pregnancy_progress/pregnancy_progress_screen.dart`\n42\t\n43\t---\n44\t\n45\t## 5. Design Tokens\n46\t\n47\t### Colors\n48\t\n49\t| Token | Hex | Usage |\n50\t|---|---|---|\n51\t| `lavenderBloom` | `#7C3AED` | Primary brand, AppBar background, primary actions |\n52\t| `blushRose` | `#F9A8D4` | Secondary accent, fruit emoji tints, mood highlights |\n53\t| `softMint` | `#6EE7B7` | Success states, positive indicators |\n54\t| `morningMist` | `#FAFAFA` | Card backgrounds |\n55\t| `lavenderTint` | `#F5F3FF` | Scaffold background |\n56\t| `deepGraphite` | `#1F2937` | Primary text |\n57\t| `stoneGrey` | `#6B7280` | Secondary text, captions, timestamps |\n58\t| `mistyBorder` | `#E5E7EB` | Borders, dividers |\n59\t| `warmWhite` | `#FFFFFF` | Bottom nav background, sheets, FAB surfaces |\n60\t\n61\t### Typography (Nunito)\n62\t\n63\t| Style | Size | Weight | Line Height | Usage |\n64\t|---|---|---|---|---|\n65\t| `displayLarge` | 57pt | Bold (700) | 64pt | Week number hero |\n66\t| `headlineMedium` | 28pt | SemiBold (600) | 36pt | Screen title |\n67\t| `titleLarge` | 22pt | SemiBold (600) | 28pt | Section headers |\n68\t| `titleMedium` | 16pt | Medium (500) | 24pt | Subtitles, list item titles |\n69\t| `bodyLarge` | 16pt | Regular (400) | 24pt | Primary body text, descriptions |\n70\t| `bodyMedium` | 14pt | Regular (400) | 20pt | Secondary text, bullet items |\n71\t| `labelLarge` | 14pt | SemiBold (600) | 20pt | Button labels, chips |\n72\t| `caption` | 11pt | Medium (500) | 16pt | Badges, timestamps |\n73\t\n74\t### Spacing (8pt base)\n75\t\n76\t| Token | Value |\n77\t|---|---|\n78\t| `xxs` | 4dp |\n79\t| `xs` | 8dp |\n80\t| `sm` | 12dp |\n81\t| `md` | 16dp |\n82\t| `lg` | 24dp |\n83\t| `xl` | 32dp |\n84\t| `xxl` | 48dp |\n85\t\n86\t### Corner Radius\n87\t\n88\t| Token | Value |\n89\t|---|---|\n90\t| `sm` | 8dp |\n91\t| `md` | 12dp |\n92\t| `lg` | 16dp |\n93\t| `full` | 999dp (pills) |\n94\t\n95\t### Motion\n96\t\n97\t| Token | Value |\n98\t|---|---|\n99\t| `durationShort` | 200ms |\n100\t| `durationMedium` | 300ms |\n101\t| `easingStandard` | `Curves.easeInOut` |\n102\t\n103\t---\n104\t\n105\t## 6. Layout Rules\n106\t\n107\t### Scaffold Structure\n108\t\n109\t```\n110\tScaffold\n111\t├── AppBar (title: \"My Pregnancy\", no elevation, Lavender Tint background)\n112\t│   └── Back button (leading) → returns to Home\n113\t├── Body: PageView (week-by-week swiper)\n114\t│   └── Each page: SingleChildScrollView\n115\t│       ├── WeekHeroCard (full-width, ~40% screen height)\n116\t│       ├── BodyChangesCard\n117\t│       ├── BabyDevelopmentCard\n118\t│       └── SelfCareTipsCard\n119\t└── Bottom: DueDateSummaryCard (pinned, always visible)\n120\t```\n121\t\n122\t### AppBar\n123\t- **Height:** Standard AppBar (56dp)\n124\t- **Background:** Lavender Tint (`#F5F3FF`)\n125\t- **Title:** \"My Pregnancy\", SemiBold 20pt, Deep Graphite\n126\t- **Leading:** Back arrow icon with 48dp touch target\n127\t- **Elevation:** 0 (transparent, blends with scaffold)\n128\t\n129\t### Body (PageView)\n130\t- **Widget:** `PageView` with `PageController`\n131\t- **Physics:** `PageScrollPhysics` (snaps to pages)\n132\t- **Initial page:** Current pregnancy week from `PregnancyProfileProvider`\n133\t- **Swipe direction:** Horizontal (left = earlier weeks, right = later weeks)\n134\t- **Cache:** Keep 1 page on each side (`PageView.cacheExtent`)\n135\t\n136\t### Bottom Card (Due Date Summary)\n137\t- **Position:** Pinned at bottom, above safe area\n138\t- **Height:** ~120dp content + bottom safe area\n139\t- **Background:** Warm White\n140\t- **Corner radius:** Top corners 28dp (bottom sheet style)\n141\t- **Shadow:** Soft diffused, 16dp blur, 4dp offset-y\n142\t\n143\t---\n144\t\n145\t## 7. Sections\n146\t\n147\t### 7.1 Week Hero Card\n148\t\n149\t**Description:** Full-width card displaying the current pregnancy week with visual fruit-size comparison and countdown to due date.\n150\t\n151\t**Widget type:** `Container` with `BoxDecoration` (rounded card, soft shadow)\n152\t\n153\t**Layout:**\n154\t```\n155\tWeekHeroCard\n156\t├── FruitEmoji (centered, 80dp size) — e.g., \"🍅\" for week 12\n157\t├── WeekNumberText (\"Week 12\", displayLarge 57pt)\n158\t├── TrimesterBadge (\"Second Trimester\", caption pill)\n159\t├── CountdownText (\"18 weeks to go\", bodyMedium, stoneGrey)\n160\t└── DueDateText (\"Due January 15, 2026\", caption, stoneGrey)\n161\t```\n162\t\n163\t**Data:**\n164\t- `currentWeek` from `PregnancyProfileProvider`\n165\t- Fruit size mapping: static catalog (week 4 = poppy seed, week 12 = lime, etc.)\n166\t- `dueDate` from `PregnancyProfileProvider`\n167\t- Trimester calculated from week number (1-13 = First, 14-26 = Second, 27-40 = Third)\n168\t\n169\t**Interactive elements:** None (static display card)\n170\t\n171\t### 7.2 Body Changes Card\n172\t\n173\t**Description:** Bulleted list of physical changes the mother may experience during this pregnancy week.\n174\t\n175\t**Widget type:** `Card` with `Column` + `Bullets` children\n176\t\n177\t**Layout:**\n178\t```\n179\tBodyChangesCard (Card, lg radius)\n180\t├── SectionHeader (\"Body Changes\", titleLarge)\n181\t└── BulletList (ListView, no scroll, bodyMedium items)\n182\t    ├── Bullet item: \"Your uterus is now about the size of a grapefruit\"\n183\t    ├── Bullet item: \"You may experience mild cramping or round ligament pain\"\n184\t    └── ...\n185\t```\n186\t\n187\t**Data:** Static `WeekContent.bodyChanges[week]` catalog (List<String>)\n188\t\n189\t**Interactive elements:** None (read-only card)\n190\t\n191\t### 7.3 Baby Development Card\n192\t\n193\t**Description:** Paragraph describing fetal development milestones for the current week.\n194\t\n195\t**Widget type:** `Card` with `Column`\n196\t\n197\t**Layout:**\n198\t```\n199\tBabyDevelopmentCard (Card, lg radius)\n200\t├── SectionHeader (\"Baby's Development\", titleLarge)\n201\t└── BodyText (bodyLarge, Deep Graphite)\n202\t    \"Your baby is now about 2 inches long — the size of a plum! \"\n203\t    \"Fingers and toes are fully formed, and tooth buds are appearing \"\n204\t    \"beneath the gums...\"\n205\t```\n206\t\n207\t**Data:** Static `WeekContent.babyDevelopment[week]` catalog (String)\n208\t\n209\t**Interactive elements:** None (read-only card)\n210\t\n211\t### 7.4 Self-Care Tips Card\n212\t\n213\t**Description:** Three actionable self-care tips for the current week. Each tip can be tapped to expand and show more detail.\n214\t\n215\t**Widget type:** `Card` with `Column` of expandable `TipTile` widgets\n216\t\n217\t**Layout:**\n218\t```\n219\tSelfCareTipsCard (Card, lg radius)\n220\t├── SectionHeader (\"Self-Care Tips\", titleLarge)\n221\t└── TipTile (expandable)\n222\t    ├── TipNumber (1, 2, 3 — blushRose circle)\n223\t    ├── TipTitle (titleMedium)\n224\t    └── TipDetail (expandable, bodyMedium) — shows on tap\n225\t```\n226\t\n227\t**Data:** Static `WeekContent.selfCareTips[week]` catalog (List<SelfCareTip>)\n228\t\n229\t**Interactive elements:**\n230\t- `TipTile` is tappable — on tap, expands/collapses `TipDetail`\n231\t- Expansion animation: 200ms ease-out, height transition\n232\t- Only one tip expanded at a time (accordion behavior)\n233\t\n234\t### 7.5 Due Date Summary Card (Bottom Pinned)\n235\t\n236\t**Description:** Fixed bottom card showing due date, days remaining, and current trimester badge.\n237\t\n238\t**Widget type:** `Container` with decorative top corners (28dp radius)\n239\t\n240\t**Layout:**\n241\t```\n242\tDueDateSummaryCard (bottom pinned)\n243\t├── TrimesterBadge (left, full pill: \"Second Trimester\")\n244\t├── DueDateLabel (\"Due Date\", caption, stoneGrey)\n245\t├── DueDateValue (\"January 15, 2026\", titleMedium)\n246\t└── DaysRemaining (\"42 days remaining\", bodyMedium, softMint for positive)\n247\t```\n248\t\n249\t**Data:** `dueDate` from `PregnancyProfileProvider`\n250\t\n251\t**Interactive elements:** None (read-only summary)\n252\t\n253\t---\n254\t\n255\t## 8. Data\n256\t\n257\t### Entities\n258\t\n259\t#### `PregnancyProfile`\n260\t| Field | Type | Source |\n261\t|---|---|---|\n262\t| `dueDate` | `DateTime` | `PregnancyProfileProvider` |\n263\t| `lastPeriodDate` | `DateTime` | `PregnancyProfileProvider` |\n264\t| `currentWeek` | `int` (computed) | `(today - dueDate + 280 days) / 7` |\n265\t\n266\t#### `WeekContent` (static catalog, keyed by week 1-40)\n267\t| Field | Type |\n268\t|---|---|\n269\t| `fruitEmoji` | `String` |\n270\t| `fruitSize` | `String` |\n271\t| `bodyChanges` | `List<String>` |\n272\t| `babyDevelopment` | `String` |\n273\t| `selfCareTips` | `List<SelfCareTip>` |\n274\t\n275\t#### `SelfCareTip`\n276\t| Field | Type |\n277\t|---|---|\n278\t| `title` | `String` |\n279\t| `detail` | `String` |\n280\t\n281\t---\n282\t\n283\t## 9. Motion\n284\t\n285\t### Page Transitions\n286\t- **Type:** Horizontal slide with PageView default physics\n287\t- **Duration:** 300ms (PageView built-in)\n288\t- **Curve:** `Curves.easeInOut`\n289\t\n290\t### Card Entrance\n291\t- **Type:** Fade + slight upward slide\n292\t- **Duration:** 300ms\n293\t- **Delay:** 50ms stagger between cards\n294\t- **Curve:** `Curves.easeOut`\n295\t\n296\t### Self-Care Tip Expansion\n297\t- **Type:** Height animation with fade\n298\t- **Duration:** 200ms\n299\t- **Curve:** `Curves.easeOut`\n300\t\n301\t### Bottom Card\n302\t- **Type:** No entrance animation (always visible)\n303\t- **Shadow:** Subtle pulse on week change — 200ms shadow intensity increase/decrease\n304\t\n305\t---\n306\t\n307\t## 10. Accessibility\n308\t\n309\t### Semantic Labels\n310\t- **Week Hero:** `\"Pregnancy week {n}, {fruitSize} size, {countdown} until due date\"`\n311\t- **Body Changes:** `\"Body changes this week: {count} items\"`\n312\t- **Baby Development:** `\"Baby development for week {n}: {description excerpt}\"`\n313\t- **Self-Care Tip:** `\"Self-care tip {n}: {title}. Tap to expand\"`\n314\t- **Due Date Summary:** `\"Due date: {date}, {days} days remaining, {trimester}\"`\n315\t- **PageView swipe:** `\"Week {n} of 40. Use swipe gestures to navigate weeks\"`\n316\t\n317\t### Focus Order\n318\t1. Back button (AppBar leading)\n319\t2. Week Hero (implicitly focusable as first content)\n320\t3. Body Changes card\n321\t4. Baby Development card\n322\t5. Self-Care Tips (each tip focusable in order)\n323\t6. Due Date Summary card\n324\t\n325\t### Contrast Notes\n326\t- All text meets WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1 minimum for body, 3:1 for large text)\n327\t- Deep Graphite (#1F2937) on Morning Mist (#FAFAFA) = 12.6:1 ✓\n328\t- Stone Grey (#6B7280) on Morning Mist = 4.7:1 ✓\n329\t- White on Lavender Bloom = 4.2:1 ✓\n330\t\n331\t---\n332\t\n333\t## 11. Anti-Patterns\n334\t\n335\t### Banned\n336\t- **No default platform colors** — all colors from design token palette\n337\t- **No arbitrary text sizing** — use type scale (57pt hero, 28pt title, 22pt section header, 16pt body)\n338\t- **No inconsistent spacing** — use 8pt base unit\n339\t- **No bottom nav** — this screen hides bottom navigation per spec\n340\t- **No FAB** — this screen has no FAB per spec\n341\t- **No hardcoded week content** — all week content from `WeekContent` catalog\n342\t- **No SliverAppBar inside PageView** — incompatible scroll physics; use standard AppBar\n343\t- **No touch targets under 48dp**\n344\t- **No pure black (#000000)** — use Deep Graphite (#1F2937)\n345\t- **No pure white (#FFFFFF) for body text** — use Deep Graphite on light surfaces\n346\t\n347\t### Constraints\n348\t- PageView cannot be nested inside another scrollable that conflicts (no SliverAppBar in same scaffold)\n349\t- Due Date Summary must not overlap content when keyboard is visible\n350\t- Week navigation must not reset expanded tip state (accordion local to each week's tip set)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b32d9a5e-04a2-474e-9641-2c2b00450d3b","uuid":"b20571f2-88a5-4420-8552-d8e445d8359a","timestamp":"2026-05-19T00:31:23.824Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/minh/Documents/openplayboosks/examples/baby-app/.stitch/designs/pregnancy-progress/SPEC.md","content":"# SPEC.md — My Pregnancy (`/pregnancy-progress`)\n\n## 1. Screen Title\n\n**My Pregnancy** — Week-by-week pregnancy progress viewer\n\n---\n\n## 2. Purpose\n\nThe Pregnancy Progress screen allows expecting mothers to explore their pregnancy journey week by week through a horizontal swiper interface. It provides:\n\n- At-a-glance view of current pregnancy week with fruit-size comparison\n- Body change expectations for each week\n- Baby development milestones\n- Actionable self-care tips tailored to each week\n- Due date tracking with countdown and trimester indicator\n\n**Why it exists:** Replaces uncertainty with knowledge — mothers can swipe to any week to understand what's happening in their body and with their baby, building confidence throughout the journey.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Route\n\n```\n/pregnancy-progress\n```\n\n- **Parent:** Home tab (`/`)\n- **Navigation type:** Push (no bottom nav, no FAB)\n- **Swipe-back:** Returns to Home\n\n---\n\n## 4. Widget Name\n\n```\nPregnancyProgressScreen\n```\n\nFile: `lib/screens/pregnancy_progress/pregnancy_progress_screen.dart`\n\n---\n\n## 5. Design Tokens\n\n### Colors\n\n| Token | Hex | Usage |\n|---|---|---|\n| `lavenderBloom` | `#7C3AED` | Primary brand, AppBar background, primary actions |\n| `blushRose` | `#F9A8D4` | Secondary accent, fruit emoji tints, mood highlights |\n| `softMint` | `#6EE7B7` | Success states, positive indicators |\n| `morningMist` | `#FAFAFA` | Card backgrounds |\n| `lavenderTint` | `#F5F3FF` | Scaffold background |\n| `deepGraphite` | `#1F2937` | Primary text |\n| `stoneGrey` | `#6B7280` | Secondary text, captions, timestamps |\n| `mistyBorder` | `#E5E7EB` | Borders, dividers |\n| `warmWhite` | `#FFFFFF` | Bottom nav background, sheets, FAB surfaces |\n\n### Typography (Nunito)\n\n| Style | Size | Weight | Line Height | Usage |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `displayLarge` | 57pt | Bold (700) | 64pt | Week number hero |\n| `headlineMedium` | 28pt | SemiBold (600) | 36pt | Screen title |\n| `titleLarge` | 22pt | SemiBold (600) | 28pt | Section headers |\n| `titleMedium` | 16pt | Medium (500) | 24pt | Subtitles, list item titles |\n| `bodyLarge` | 16pt | Regular (400) | 24pt | Primary body text, descriptions |\n| `bodyMedium` | 14pt | Regular (400) | 20pt | Secondary text, bullet items |\n| `labelLarge` | 14pt | SemiBold (600) | 20pt | Button labels, chips |\n| `caption` | 11pt | Medium (500) | 16pt | Badges, timestamps |\n\n### Spacing (8pt base)\n\n| Token | Value |\n|---|---|\n| `xxs` | 4dp |\n| `xs` | 8dp |\n| `sm` | 12dp |\n| `md` | 16dp |\n| `lg` | 24dp |\n| `xl` | 32dp |\n| `xxl` | 48dp |\n\n### Corner Radius\n\n| Token | Value |\n|---|---|\n| `sm` | 8dp |\n| `md` | 12dp |\n| `lg` | 16dp |\n| `full` | 999dp (pills) |\n\n### Motion\n\n| Token | Value |\n|---|---|\n| `durationShort` | 200ms |\n| `durationMedium` | 300ms |\n| `easingStandard` | `Curves.easeInOut` |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Layout Rules\n\n### Scaffold Structure\n\n```\nScaffold\n├── AppBar (title: \"My Pregnancy\", no elevation, Lavender Tint background)\n│   └── Back button (leading) → returns to Home\n├── Body: PageView (week-by-week swiper)\n│   └── Each page: SingleChildScrollView\n│       ├── WeekHeroCard (full-width, ~40% screen height)\n│       ├── BodyChangesCard\n│       ├── BabyDevelopmentCard\n│       └── SelfCareTipsCard\n└── Bottom: DueDateSummaryCard (pinned, always visible)\n```\n\n### AppBar\n- **Height:** Standard AppBar (56dp)\n- **Background:** Lavender Tint (`#F5F3FF`)\n- **Title:** \"My Pregnancy\", SemiBold 20pt, Deep Graphite\n- **Leading:** Back arrow icon with 48dp touch target\n- **Elevation:** 0 (transparent, blends with scaffold)\n\n### Body (PageView)\n- **Widget:** `PageView` with `PageController`\n- **Physics:** `PageScrollPhysics` (snaps to pages)\n- **Initial page:** Current pregnancy week from `PregnancyProfileProvider`\n- **Swipe direction:** Horizontal (left = earlier weeks, right = later weeks)\n- **Cache:** Keep 1 page on each side (`PageView.cacheExtent`)\n\n### Bottom Card (Due Date Summary)\n- **Position:** Pinned at bottom, above safe area\n- **Height:** ~120dp content + bottom safe area\n- **Background:** Warm White\n- **Corner radius:** Top corners 28dp (bottom sheet style)\n- **Shadow:** Soft diffused, 16dp blur, 4dp offset-y\n\n---\n\n## 7. Sections\n\n### 7.1 Week Hero Card\n\n**Description:** Full-width card displaying the current pregnancy week with visual fruit-size comparison and countdown to due date.\n\n**Widget type:** `Container` with `BoxDecoration` (rounded card, soft shadow)\n\n**Layout:**\n```\nWeekHeroCard\n├── FruitEmoji (centered, 80dp size) — e.g., \"🍅\" for week 12\n├── WeekNumberText (\"Week 12\", displayLarge 57pt)\n├── TrimesterBadge (\"Second Trimester\", caption pill)\n├── CountdownText (\"18 weeks to go\", bodyMedium, stoneGrey)\n└── DueDateText (\"Due January 15, 2026\", caption, stoneGrey)\n```\n\n**Data:**\n- `currentWeek` from `PregnancyProfileProvider`\n- Fruit size mapping: static catalog (week 4 = poppy seed, week 12 = lime, etc.)\n- `dueDate` from `PregnancyProfileProvider`\n- Trimester calculated from week number (1-13 = First, 14-26 = Second, 27-40 = Third)\n\n**Interactive elements:** None (static display card)\n\n### 7.2 Body Changes Card\n\n**Description:** Bulleted list of physical changes the mother may experience during this pregnancy week.\n\n**Widget type:** `Card` with `Column` + `Bullets` children\n\n**Layout:**\n```\nBodyChangesCard (Card, lg radius)\n├── SectionHeader (\"Body Changes\", titleLarge)\n└── BulletList (ListView, no scroll, bodyMedium items)\n    ├── Bullet item: \"Your uterus is now about the size of a grapefruit\"\n    ├── Bullet item: \"You may experience mild cramping or round ligament pain\"\n    └── ...\n```\n\n**Data:** Static `WeekContent.bodyChanges[week]` catalog (List<String>)\n\n**Interactive elements:** None (read-only card)\n\n### 7.3 Baby Development Card\n\n**Description:** Paragraph describing fetal development milestones for the current week.\n\n**Widget type:** `Card` with `Column`\n\n**Layout:**\n```\nBabyDevelopmentCard (Card, lg radius)\n├── SectionHeader (\"Baby's Development\", titleLarge)\n└── BodyText (bodyLarge, Deep Graphite)\n    \"Your baby is now about 2 inches long — the size of a plum! \"\n    \"Fingers and toes are fully formed, and tooth buds are appearing \"\n    \"beneath the gums...\"\n```\n\n**Data:** Static `WeekContent.babyDevelopment[week]` catalog (String)\n\n**Interactive elements:** None (read-only card)\n\n### 7.4 Self-Care Tips Card\n\n**Description:** Three actionable self-care tips for the current week. Each tip can be tapped to expand and show more detail.\n\n**Widget type:** `Card` with `Column` of expandable `TipTile` widgets\n\n**Layout:**\n```\nSelfCareTipsCard (Card, lg radius)\n├── SectionHeader (\"Self-Care Tips\", titleLarge)\n└── TipTile (expandable)\n    ├── TipNumber (1, 2, 3 — blushRose circle)\n    ├── TipTitle (titleMedium)\n    └── TipDetail (expandable, bodyMedium) — shows on tap\n```\n\n**Data:** Static `WeekContent.selfCareTips[week]` catalog (List<SelfCareTip>)\n\n**Interactive elements:**\n- `TipTile` is tappable — on tap, expands/collapses `TipDetail`\n- Expansion animation: 200ms ease-out, height transition\n- Only one tip expanded at a time (accordion behavior)\n\n### 7.5 Due Date Summary Card (Bottom Pinned)\n\n**Description:** Fixed bottom card showing due date, days remaining, and current trimester badge.\n\n**Widget type:** `Container` with decorative top corners (28dp radius)\n\n**Layout:**\n```\nDueDateSummaryCard (bottom pinned)\n├── TrimesterBadge (left, full pill: \"Second Trimester\")\n├── DueDateLabel (\"Due Date\", caption, stoneGrey)\n├── DueDateValue (\"January 15, 2026\", titleMedium)\n└── DaysRemaining (\"42 days remaining\", bodyMedium, softMint for positive)\n```\n\n**Data:** `dueDate` from `PregnancyProfileProvider`\n\n**Interactive elements:** None (read-only summary)\n\n---\n\n## 8. Data\n\n### Entities\n\n#### `PregnancyProfile`\n| Field | Type | Source |\n|---|---|---|\n| `dueDate` | `DateTime` | `PregnancyProfileProvider` |\n| `lastPeriodDate` | `DateTime` | `PregnancyProfileProvider` |\n| `currentWeek` | `int` (computed) | `(today - dueDate + 280 days) / 7` |\n\n#### `WeekContent` (static catalog, keyed by week 1-40)\n| Field | Type |\n|---|---|\n| `fruitEmoji` | `String` |\n| `fruitSize` | `String` |\n| `bodyChanges` | `List<String>` |\n| `babyDevelopment` | `String` |\n| `selfCareTips` | `List<SelfCareTip>` |\n\n#### `SelfCareTip`\n| Field | Type |\n|---|---|\n| `title` | `String` |\n| `detail` | `String` |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Motion\n\n### Page Transitions\n- **Type:** Horizontal slide with PageView default physics\n- **Duration:** 300ms (PageView built-in)\n- **Curve:** `Curves.easeInOut`\n\n### Card Entrance\n- **Type:** Fade + slight upward slide\n- **Duration:** 300ms\n- **Delay:** 50ms stagger between cards\n- **Curve:** `Curves.easeOut`\n\n### Self-Care Tip Expansion\n- **Type:** Height animation with fade\n- **Duration:** 200ms\n- **Curve:** `Curves.easeOut`\n\n### Bottom Card\n- **Type:** No entrance animation (always visible)\n- **Shadow:** Subtle pulse on week change — 200ms shadow intensity increase/decrease\n\n---\n\n## 10. Accessibility\n\n### Semantic Labels\n- **Week Hero:** `\"Pregnancy week {n}, {fruitSize} size, {countdown} until due date\"`\n- **Body Changes:** `\"Body changes this week: {count} items\"`\n- **Baby Development:** `\"Baby development for week {n}: {description excerpt}\"`\n- **Self-Care Tip:** `\"Self-care tip {n}: {title}. Tap to expand\"`\n- **Due Date Summary:** `\"Due date: {date}, {days} days remaining, {trimester}\"`\n- **PageView swipe:** `\"Week {n} of 40. Use swipe gestures to navigate weeks\"`\n\n### Focus Order\n1. Back button (AppBar leading)\n2. Week Hero (implicitly focusable as first content)\n3. Body Changes card\n4. Baby Development card\n5. Self-Care Tips (each tip focusable in order)\n6. Due Date Summary card\n\n### Contrast Notes\n- All text meets WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1 minimum for body, 3:1 for large text)\n- Deep Graphite (#1F2937) on Morning Mist (#FAFAFA) = 12.6:1 ✓\n- Stone Grey (#6B7280) on Morning Mist = 4.7:1 ✓\n- White on Lavender Bloom = 4.2:1 ✓\n\n---\n\n## 11. Anti-Patterns\n\n### Banned\n- **No default platform colors** — all colors from design token palette\n- **No arbitrary text sizing** — use type scale (57pt hero, 28pt title, 22pt section header, 16pt body)\n- **No inconsistent spacing** — use 8pt base unit\n- **No bottom nav** — this screen hides bottom navigation per spec\n- **No FAB** — this screen has no FAB per spec\n- **No hardcoded week content** — all week content from `WeekContent` catalog\n- **No SliverAppBar inside PageView** — incompatible scroll physics; use standard AppBar\n- **No touch targets under 48dp**\n- **No pure black (#000000)** — use Deep Graphite (#1F2937)\n- **No pure white (#FFFFFF) for body text** — use Deep Graphite on light surfaces\n\n### Constraints\n- PageView cannot be nested inside another scrollable that conflicts (no SliverAppBar in same scaffold)\n- Due Date Summary must not overlap content when keyboard is visible\n- Week navigation must not reset expanded tip state (accordion local to each week's tip set)","numLines":350,"startLine":1,"totalLines":350}}}
